{"/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_electrum_ver02/data/sn95060997/00517018934/1910110401/0253.xml":{"full_text":"Arizona Range News.\nVOL. XVII\nMASCOT COPPER ISSUES ANNUAL REPORT\nHAS BEEN MAILED TO STOCKHOLDERS\nSUBSTANTIAL CONDITIONS AT PROPERTY\nThis Company is Developing What\nis Destined to be One of the\nBiggest Copper Mines\nin the Country\nAN UNUSUAL PROPERTY\nMore Like a Manufacturing Enterprise Than\na Mining Enterprise as Generally Un\nderstood, and Will Be a Great\nWealth Producer For\nMany Generations\nOne of the most satisfactory reports\never issued by a mining company has\nbeen mailed to stockholders by the\nMascot Copper Company, following the\nannual meeting of the corporation at\n\u2022Chicago, on October 3rd.\nA perusal of the report which appears\nin this issue of the Arizona Range\nNews should prove a source of intense\nsatisfaction to all who have shown their\nfaith in the magnificent property of\nMascot Copper by making investments\nin the shares of the company now\noperating in Dos Cabezas in the heart\nof the greatest copper zone of the\nUnited States.\nAlthough the company has not yet\nreached the producing stage, the official\nreport just sent to the stockholders\nshows that the property is being de\nveloped and equipped in a substantial\nand permanent manner preparatory to\ntaking its place among the largest pro\nducing copper mines of the world.\nBasing future events upon the happen\nings of the past, it will not be many\nmonths before this company will enter\nupon a producing era that will come to\nthe vast majority of investors in cop-\n\\w ^SSIHMMI' Wl\u00ae EH -OB*\nMMrggg MM\u25a0MkV^ ''\u2018V^\u2022& \u2019BB M IBS\nIB* >\u25a0\u2022'^Hb HH^ v T \u2019\u2019\u00aewi\njMMEj\u00df&|i||jft\u00dfM\u00dfM OmHHhRBI BBMjBMM ^ih- 2 iBJ\n4 j. g> 4Bp Ew^J\n|Bt|^-^MgM^ jM MM MB |m&X;'||^^\n||?y-. \u2022'j d &.-M. H w\nwKKs^ v? t\u00a7 -2 S^HKekS^HmbHmHSS|h|\nThe Hoist at the Three-Compartment Air Shift.\nWILLCOX, COCHISE COUNTY, ARIZONA, FRIDAY, NOVEMBER 4, 1910\nper shares as a revelation; but to the\nreaders of this paper it will be accepted\nsimply as a confirmation of the predic\ntion that we have been reiterating for\nmany months \u2014that at Dos Cabezas the\nMascot Copper Company is developing\nwhat is destined to be one of the great\nest copper producers of the country.\nWe have preached this gospel because\nwe know it to be so, and Hon. H. H.\nEvans, president of the company, could\nnot have given expression to more\npertinent remarks than those contained\nin the closing paragraph of the annual\nreport, the significance of which we\ncan readily comprehend, both from the\nstandpoint of a stockholddr in the Mas\ncot Company and as one having busi\nness interests here. Mr. Evans said:\nStockholders Congratulated\n\u201cWe feel that all shareholders are\nto be congratulated on the present sub\nstantial conditions at the property, to\ngether with the economical manage\nment during the past year, and have\nevery reason to believe that with the\ncontinued hearty support of the stock\nholders your directors will be able to\nLoaded Ore Cars From the Consolidated Tunnel.\nreport at the next annual meeting in\nformation of a character that will be\nquite interesting in a financial way to\nall interested parties.\u201d\nWhile the citizens of this community\nare not all stockholders in the Mascot\nCopper Company, there is probably not\na man, woman or child but what will be\nbenefitted indirectly by the successful\nculmination of the operations being\nconducted by this company in our very\nmidst. The benefits to be derived are\ntoo numerous for us to mention in de\ntail, but briefly it means a permanent\nhome market for all our products, en\nhanced real estate values and prosper\nity for our business men. So, while, as\nPresident Evans says, \u2018all shareholders\nare to be congratulated on account of\nthe present substantial conditions at\nthe property,\u201d the citizens of this com\nmunity are also in line for congratula\ntions owing to the same reason.\nMineral Means Wealth\nThe history of most every mountain\nregion commences with the develop-\nment of its mineral resources, and\nmineral spells wealth \u2014what we are all\nstriving for. We have been told that\n\u201cthe love of money is the root of all\nevil, but that statement is far from\nthe truth. The savage has no love of\nwealth and, except for slight mention\nin our records, he passes off the earth\nleaving behind him not a scintilla of\nevidence of his having existed. The\ncriminals whom we discipline for their\nevil acts are those who do not think\nenough of money to work for it, and\nwithout appreciation of it there would\nbe no civilization; we would be a people\nwithout a history.\nTurning back the scroll of time, we\nfind all records closely associated with\nthe mineral industry. The magnificent\ncities on the Nile and the Euphrates\nwere built with the money taken from\nthe mines. Miners were employed in\nlarge numbers at Mt. Sinai at the ac\ncession of Menes to the throne of Egypt,\n3400 years B. C. W. M. Flinders-\nPetrie gives an account and an illustra\ntion in a recent article of \u201cpart of a\ntablet of a record with names of 100\nminers 2500 years B. C.;\u201d and he says\nin speaking of this and other tablets\nfound at Sinai: \u201cEach king who ordered\nan expedition had his name and the\naccount of his work carved over his\nmine. Thus are found Sanekht and\nZeser of the third dynasty and many\nothers down to the eighteenth dynasty,\nshowing that the mines were worked\nfrom 4500 to 1500 years B. C.\u201d\nHistory Repeats Itself\nWithout appreciation of mineral\nwealth we will retrograde. History\nrepeats itself. The valley of the Nile,\nthe Tigris and the Euphrates are as\nI fertile today as they ever were,\nbut where once were thriving commu\nnities, where great irrigation projects\nwere utilized to make the land \u201cblos\ni som as a rose,\u201d one may look over des\nolate wastes as far as the eye can\nreach. Why? Because the mining in\ndustry was allowed to languish, the\n\u2022people went off to new finds, and the\nfarmer could not live with no one to\nraise provisions for but himself.\nUnlike the farmers of those days,\nwho were subject to the caprices of\ngold mining, which created only tempo\nrary flourishing camps, the citizens of\nthis community have in Mascot a vast\nand rich copper field where develop-\nments to date give every assurance of\npermanency.\nWill Endure For Generations\nAs history has proven, the copper\nmines are more like manufacturing\nenterprises than like mining enterprises\nas generally understood, because the\nelement of risk is practically eliminated.\nIn gold mines it is exceptional to find\nmore than a few years\u2019 ore supply. In\nthe case of a copper mine, such as we\nare discussing, the tonnage of ore, now\nproven to exist beyond all reasonable\ndoubt, is so great as to assure a con\ntinuous life for the property for a\nperiod long after several generations of\nthe human race have ceased to endure.\nAs a result the scale of operations can\nbe planned with a view to the largest\neventual profit in the case of a copper\nmine like Mascot, where with the aver\nage gold mine this cannot be done with\nthe same assurance of stability, and\nthe result is that, as a class, copper\nmines produce more permanent and\nlarger dividends and, as a natural con\nsequence, the towns that spring up\naround the large copper camps are also\npermanent and more prosperous.\nIt sometimes happens that a copper\ncamp has to cease operations tempor\narily during a business depression or\nlow price of the metal. But this occurs\nwhere the copper content is low and\nthere are no gold and silver values to\nspeak of, only the copper alone to de\npend upon. In the case of Mascot there\nwill be no cessation of production for\nthe reason that this camp\u2019s ore contains\na higher percentage of copper, relative\nly speaking, besides sufficient gold and\nsilver to defray the expense of mining.\nSo regardless of what business condi\ntions might be or what the price of the\nmetal, this company would continue to\noperate its mines at a handsome profit.\nRegarding The Possible Profits\nAs we have, in former articles, given\nsome idea of the immense tonnage con\nfined in the vast holdings now being\ndeveloped by the Mascot Copper Com\npany, we will not at this time touch\nupon this point in detail. Instead, we\nwill present a map of the camp showing\nthe various veins of rich copper ore\nthat exist on the property. Some idea\nmay be gained of the future possibili\nties of the camp as a producer of the\nConcluded on page 4.\nNO. 34","height":"24627","width":"16380"}}
